    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix MSG3 payload preparation in non-SA modes\n\n### Summary\nThe `nr_rrc_prepare_msg3_payload` function was not preparing RRC connection setup requests in NSA mode because of an overly restrictive mode check. When the MAC layer indicated that MSG3 payload preparation was needed, the function would return early without preparing the payload if the UE was not in SA mode.\n\nThis fix removes the unnecessary mode check, allowing MSG3 payloads to be prepared in all modes when requested by the MAC layer.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair2/RRC/NR_UE/rrc_UE.c`: Removed the `IS_SA_MODE` check from `nr_rrc_prepare_msg3_payload` function\n\n### Reproduction\nTo reproduce the issue:\n1. Configure UE in NSA mode\n2. Trigger an RRC connection setup procedure\n3. Observe that MAC layer requests MSG3 payload preparation via `NR_RRC_MAC_MSG3_IND`\n4. The `nr_rrc_prepare_msg3_payload` function returns early without preparing the payload\n5. Connection setup fails due to missing MSG3 payload\n\nWith the fix, the MSG3 payload is prepared correctly in all modes when requested by the MAC layer.\n"
}